import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df = pd.read_csv("../data/features/song_features.csv")
df


for album, sub in df.groupby("album"):
    plt.scatter(
        sub["repetition_rate"],
        sub["lexical_entropy"],
        label=album,
        s=80,
        alpha=0.75
    )

plt.xlabel("Repetition Rate (Structure)")
plt.ylabel("Lexical Entropy (Surprise)")
plt.title("Structure vs Surprise in Lana Del Rey Songs")
plt.legend()
plt.show()


## Interpretation

Rather than treating structure and randomness as opposing forces,
this visualization suggests that songs cluster within a bounded
region of the structure–surprise space. Songs from *Born to Die*
tend to show higher repetition with lower entropy, while *Norman
F***ing Rockwell!* exhibits greater lexical variability.

This supports the idea of a shifting balance — or “sweet spot” —
between formal constraint and unpredictability across albums.


